Synthetise data as a function of defined Epoch

Source: R/Epoch_SliceR.R
Epoch_SliceR.Rd

This function will synthetise (i.e., compute the mean of) defined column(s) from a data frame depending on a specified epoch (i.e., a time interval over which we want to synthetise the data).

Usage

Epoch_SliceR(
  df,
  ID,
  columns_to_synthesize,
  epoch_length,
  sample_rate,
  session_duration
)

Arguments

df

a data frame containing the data we want to synthetise at a defined epoch-level

ID

a column from the data frame referencing the unique participants' identifiers

columns_to_synthesize

columns of the data frame that we wish to synthetise at the epoch-level

epoch_length

time duration over which we want to synthetise the data (in seconds)

sample_rate

sample rate of the protocol

session_duration

duration of the whole protocol

Value

a data frame that should be shorter.
